danger lights is a 1930 american pre-code drama film , directed by george b. seitz , from a screenplay by james ashmore creelman .   it stars louis wolheim , robert armstrong , and jean arthur .   the plot concerns railroading on the chicago , milwaukee , st. paul and pacific railroad , and the movie was largely filmed along that railroad 's lines in montana .   the railway yard in miles city , montana was a primary setting , while rural scenes were shot along the railway line through sixteen mile canyon , montana .   additional footage was shot in chicago , illinois .   the film was the first ever shot in the new spoor-berggren natural vision process .